{
  "texts": [
    "Initially, word segmentation was performed to split the text into individual words or tokens.",
    "This step is crucial as it helps identify meaningful units for further analysis.",
    "Stop words, which are commonly used words that do not contribute much to the overall meaning, were then removed to reduce noise and improve analysis efficiency.",
    "Lemmatization was also applied to reduce words to their base or dictionary forms, allowing for effective comparison and analysis.",
    "Furthermore, named entity recognition techniques were employed to identify and categorize specific information such as names, locations, organizations, and events."
  ]
}